Postal zip codes are a system of codes used by post offices and shipping companies to identify a particular postal district or town. The codes, which vary in length and format depending on the country and organization used, are also sometimes referred to as postal codes. They are commonly used in place of the complete postal address if that information is not needed.

In Iran, postal zip codes have been used since 1975 and are administrated by the Islamic Republic of Iran
